<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/styles.css"></head><body class="usual"><div class="navline"><a href="/hackchallenge.php" title="Go to the challenge-list."><img src="/files/images/icons/list_small.gif" width="12" height="11" alt="icon" title="Go to the challenge-list." /><span>Challenges</span></a><img src="/files/images/misc/arrow_navline.gif" class="arrow" width="10" height="9" alt="-&gt;" title="" /><span>Science</span><img src="/files/images/misc/arrow_navline.gif" class="arrow" width="10" height="9" alt="-&gt;" title="" /><a href="/challenges/science/prism/index.php" title="Challenge: &quot;Prisms&quot;"><span>Prisms</span></a></div><div class="module"><div class="chall_header"><table cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="info"><img class="grouppic" alt="a Science-challenge" src="/files/images/groupmasters/11_all.gif" height="18" width="25" /><span>Science 3: &quot;Prisms&quot;</span></td><td class="links"><table cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="forum"><a href="/challvote.php?challid=101" title="Rate this challenge!"><img src="/files/images/icons/vote_stat_sl.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="vote icon" title="Rate this challenge!" /><span>Vote</span></a></td><td class="forum_space">&nbsp;</td><td class="forum"><a href="/forum/forum_showforum.php?forumid=29&amp;challenge_id=101" title="Visit the Science-Forum to ask questions or to find hints for this challenge."><img src="/files/images/misc/challenge_forum_questions.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="forum icon" title="Visit the Science-Forum to ask questions or to find hints for this challenge." /><span>Forum</span></a></td><td class="forum_space">&nbsp;</td><td class="forum"><a href="/forum/forum_showforum.php?forumid=40&amp;challenge_id=101" title="Visit the Science-Forum for solutions of this challenge."><img src="/files/images/misc/challenge_forum_solutions.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="forum icon" title="Visit the Science-Forum for solutions of this challenge." /><span>Solutions</span></a></td><td class="done">done&nbsp;<a href="/challengestats.php?challengeid=101" title="156 users have solved this challenge so far.">[156]</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></div><div class="challenge_div">A certain crane shall hold some objects which have the shape of a prism. These prisms have an isosceles triangle as base:<div class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;"><img class="challenge_1" src="prisma.png" alt="sketch" /></div>The shaded area is the prism (the picture shows a cut through it). The crane has two &quot;arms&quot; which shall hold these prisms by pressing them from each side. These forces are the red ones in the sketch and they work right-angled to the side-faces of the prism(s). Task 1:<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">Depending on the static friction value &mu;, the prisms the crane is able to carry are limited to those which have certain angles &alpha;. Get an equation which shows the relation between &mu; and the possible &alpha;'s; solved to &alpha;. Something like this: &quot;&alpha;&gt;2&middot;&mu;&quot;.</p>Task two:<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">Which force must the crane excert on a certain prism to be able to carry it? Derive a nice formula which contains all the variables &agrave; la &quot;F=m+g&middot;&mu;<sup>&alpha;</sup>-45&quot;</p>Put all the stuff together and <a class="challenge_1" href="/forum/forum_newtopic.php?forumid=50&amp;challenge=101">post your solution with explanation here!</a>
</div></div></body></html>